This cultural signature is accompanied by the development of the writer Moleskine: recently the brand opened the exhibition "Zacházka", where architects or artists exhibit their notebook.
In August, on the occasion of the Locarn Film Festival, she also presented new records to a leopard-like writer.
Moleskine profits from its success and this cultural aura and diversifys its products: bags, diaries, pencils, bookcases ... The label extends to a whole range of carriers.
Success that sparked envy: in autumn 2006 Modo Modo was bought by SG Capital Europe Investment Funds, today Syntegra Capital, writing a new page in the history of Moleskine.
