Finally, long-term unemployment is very widespread: 53% of disabled people are 38% on average.
In short, these are the criteria which make it particularly difficult to return to work and which constitute the "core of the problem", according to Christian Grapin, Director General of Tremplin Association, which was established in 1992 to help businesses receive disabled workers.
